Aleatoricism the incorporation chance into the process creation especially the creation art media The word derives from the Latin word alea the rolling dice Aleatory should not confused with either improvisation indeterminacy Charles Hartman discusses several methods automatic generation poetry his book The Virtual Muse The term aleatory music was first coined Werner MeyerEppler 1955 describe course sound events that determined general but depends chance detail When his article was published English the translator mistakenly rendered his German noun Aleatorik adjective and inadvertently created new English word aleatoric Pierre Boulez applied the term this sense his own pieces distinguish them from the indeterminate music John Cage While Boulez purposefully composed his pieces allow the performer certain liberties with regard the sequencing and repetition parts Cage often composed through the application chance operations without allowing the performer liberties Another prolific composer aleatory music was Karlheinz Stockhausen Aleatoric techniques are sometimes used contemporary film music Examples can found John Williamss scores well for example Mark Snows music for XFiles Fight the Future filmmaking there are several avantgarde examples one Andy Vodas Chance Chants which features Allison Knowles computer poem House Dust Fred Campers 1984 first screening 2002 uses coinflipping for one section determine which three possible reels screen and what order they should 3360 permutations Film scholar Barry Salt directed the 1971 film Six Reels Film Shown Any Order 